Those experiences strengthened Abraham’s faith.
Can we build a friendship with Jehovah?
We can indeed! The needed knowledge and experience are readily available.
Abraham had only a fraction of the abundant riches of wisdom now contained in the Bible.
God’s Word is full of treasures that can deepen our knowledge about the Maker of heaven and earth and help us to build respect and love for him.
As such feelings move us to obey God, we gain experience because we see how obeying him works out.
We find that his counsel protects us and that he blesses and strengthens us.
We learn that wholehearted service to God brings fulfillment, peace, and joy.
As we grow in such knowledge and experience, our faith in Jehovah and our friendship with him grow as well.
