Now David stood before Jonathan’s father, King Saul of Israel, with the head of the Philistine in his hand.
Jonathan probably admired David for his courage.
It was clear that God was with David, and Jonathan and David became bound together in close friendship.
In fact, they made a covenant because Jonathan loved David as himself.
For the rest of his life, he was loyal to David.
Jonathan’s attachment to David endured, even though God had chosen David to be Israel’s next king.
Jonathan became concerned about David when Saul was seeking to kill him.
