In his program of personal study, he continually searches for Scriptural principles that can help him to distinguish right from wrong.
Thereafter, when he makes decisions, he gives evidence of spiritual maturity.
For instance, he listens to his Bible-trained conscience.
The mature Christian shows humility in that he recognizes that Jehovah’s ways and standards are always better than his own.
